\chapter{Zaire}

Not to be confused with Postage stamps and postal history of the Republic of the Congo (a former French colony).


This is a survey of the postage stamps and postal history of the Democratic Republic of the Congo, formerly 
Zaire and the Belgian Congo.

Belgian Congo

The [Belgian Congo](../belgian-congo/introduction) started life as the Congo Free State becoming 
the Belgian Congo in 1907.

\section{Zaire}

The first stamps of Zaire were issued on 18 December 1971.[1]

Democratic Republic of the Congo

In 1997 the country changed name to the Democratic Republic of the Congo.


                                  
